# File naming: kebab-case

Use **kebab-case** for filenames across this repo unless an ecosystem convention overrides it.

## Do

- Component modules: `product-card.tsx`, `mobile-filters-sheet.tsx`, `nav.tsx`
- Hooks: `use-product-params.ts`, `use-cart.ts`
- Utilities and services: `get-products.ts`, `format-price.ts`
- Co-located styles or tests next to those names: `product-card.test.tsx`

## Don’t

- PascalCase filenames: `ProductCard.tsx`, `MobileFiltersSheet.tsx`
- Mixed or unclear casing for new files

Exported **symbols** (components, functions, types) stay in **PascalCase** / usual TypeScript conventions; only the **file path** is kebab-case.

## Exceptions (keep upstream / framework names)

- **Next.js App Router** special files where the segment name is fixed: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `route.ts`, `template.tsx`, `default.tsx`, `opengraph-image.tsx`, etc.
- **Root/config** files that tools expect by exact name: `next.config.ts`, `postcss.config.mjs`, `proxy.ts`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `README.md`, and similar.
- **Prisma**: `schema.prisma` and migration folder names generated by Prisma.
- **`package.json`**, lockfiles, and other package-manager standard names.

When adding a new file, default to kebab-case and only deviate when it matches one of the exceptions above.
